    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed or flagged; 7 factors assessed with achieved levels below required levels, 6 factors not assessed due to epistemic gaps at MRL 5. The assessment package is structurally complete and the evidence base has been reviewed against ASME V&V 40-2018 requirements. The hemolysis prediction methodology references Soares et al. (2024) Methods (https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) for the power-law calibration protocol; this citation informs the model-form factor rationale. Overall credibility is insufficient for regulatory submission but the assessment itself is accepted as complete for internal review purposes.",
